706776f-a.text:
Shore Road, east side, at 79th Street. From right to left, a view of the homes of W. R. and A. Bennett, facing Shore Road. In the foreground is a coffer dam in connection with the building of a new sewer outlet.
About 1917.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

706777f-a.text:
(1)
Shore Road, at the N.E. corner of 79th Street, showing the J. Remsen Bennett house, which was erected about 1862. This house was owned by David C. Bennett in 1912: in 1917, it was sold to a group of realtors. The house no longer appears on the 1929 maps of Brooklyn.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
(2)
TThe same, from the south side.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
